Content: ## Key Concepts

### Training and Testing
In machine learning, datasets are typically split into training and testing sets. The training set is used to train the model, while the testing set is used to evaluate its performance on unseen data. This helps prevent overfitting, where a model performs well on training data but poorly on new data.
